    entry_requirements = '<div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>Students must maintain a grade point average of 5 or above to remain in the program. Those who do not maintain this average will be transferred to the Bachelor of Social Science.\<br/>\n<br/>\nYou can choose from the following majors:</p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>As a graduate of this degree, you can look forward to a broad range of exciting career opportunities in different sectors and industries. Below are some examples of the possible careers you can pursue with this degree:</p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<ul><li>Cultural tourism</li><li>Community work</li><li>Teaching (with further study)</li><li>International development agencies</li><li>Government agencies</li><li>Travel planning and tour directing<br/>\n</li></ul>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>"There were many aspects of Western that I like, especially that campus is close to home. I love that there are jobs on-campus for students."<br/>\n<b style="\tfont-size: 1.0pc;\n"><br/>\n— May Willard, Bachelor of Social Science</b></p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>Applicants who have undertaken studies overseas may have to provide proof of proficiency in English. Local applicants who are applying through the Universities Admissions Centre (UAC) will find details of minimum English proficiency requirements and acceptable proof on the UAC website. Local applicants applying directly to the University should also use the information provided on the UAC website. <a href="https://www.uac.edu.au/undergraduate/courses/ws/727610.shtml" rel="noopener nor